 Tonto Dikeh has taken to her social media accounts to sensitise her fans on coronavirus after losing two acquaintances in two days. The controversial actress took to her Instagram page to share her experience with the deadly Coronavirus saying the virus is not on a break. The actress warned her 6.1 million fans on Instagram and the general public to take the virus seriously and follow all protective measures to curb the spread. She wrote: “lost an acquaintance yesterday, lost one just now. COVID 19 isn’t on break guys, it ain’t no myth shit is fucking real”. This is coming a few days after Psquare half, Peter Okoye, announced that he, alongside his wife and daughter, recently tested positive to the virus. 